				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, Sony has finally made me come to the level where I am going to shut up, and I hope some of the forward thinking bards out there will do the same.
<br />

<br />
Stop telling stuff guys, it just gets us nerfed.
<br />

<br />
AE kiting- been around forever,then it gets big press on our boards and others, and wham it gets a nerf, the third in a row, now it's gone.
<br />

<br />
Lull duration-
<br />
Manapumping-
<br />
Illusions and faction-
<br />

<br />
Do I need to go on?
<br />

<br />
It used to be, we all shared our knowledge and our strategies like good Bards, but all it seems to get us is idiots abusing things, it becoming commonplace, and it going away.
<br />

<br />
You got a good idea about how to use the new charm? How to use the mob restrictions for our AE's? Great! Tell your friends in game, send them an email, call them on the phone.
<br />

<br />
Tell them on a board and it's gonna get nerfed. Using our abilities to their fullest, being cutting edge, using ALL our tools in ways not thought of by Sony are just not acceptable to them.
<br />

<br />
Stop advertising it.
<br />

<br />
It's a tough impulse to resist , I know, I have also done it.
<br />
No longer-
<br />

<br />
Just ask yourself one question before you post when someone asks &quot;How do I do this?&quot;
<br />
Does the ability feel really good, does it empower you beyond what another class can do easily?
<br />
If it does, and you post it, expect SoE to read it, and examine it for the nerfbat, and we all know they have ZERO problem swinging that.</span></td>
